<section id='project-content' class='wrapper group row'>
	<div class='project-text six columns'>
		<p>Recording how neighborhoods change can be difficult. Snapshots from the ground provide on view, but overhead images can capture a larger scope and a perspective on new developments that aren't accessible from the street or sidewalk.</p>
		<p>This project looks at construction on Telegraph Avenue and in Berkeley's Sproul Plaza. It provides a record of the work being done and what the skyline and aerial perspective on the neighborhood looks like. As it continues, it will show the continuous growth of this neighborhood and provide insight into how UC Berkeley and the city of Berkeley can work together to make the intersection of Telegraph Avenue and the campus a thriving, vibrant neighborhood.</p>
	</div>
